  <rte>
    <name>A Combe Gill circuit from Seatoller</name>
    <desc>On paper this appears to be an easy Lake District walk amidst some of the lesser heights of Lakeland. However it requires excellent navigational skills in bad weather and involves a steep ascent on grass in the early stages of the walk.</desc>
    <author>Copyright Walking Britain</author>
	<url>www.walkingbritain.co.uk/walk-1175-description</url>
